        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 1:10PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 110 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Trinidad, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Trinidad, Cokedale, Starkville, Gulnare, Boncarbo, Segundo, Hoehne,
Raton Pass, and Weston.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
